<subpara id="RM000001GEV00RX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000001GEV00RX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00004UA00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT REAR WIPER MOTOR ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the wiper operation.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B117882E03" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s3>
<ptxt>Connect the battery's positive (+) lead to terminal 1 (B) and the negative (-) lead to terminal 2 (+1), and check that the motor operates.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Motor operates.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the motor assembly.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the automatic stop operation.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Connect the battery's positive (+) lead to terminal 1 (B) and the negative (-) lead to terminal 2 (+1). With the motor rotating, disconnect terminal 1 (B) to stop the wiper motor operation at the automatic stop position.</ptxt>
</s3>
<s3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B117887E04" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Check that the motor stops automatically at the automatic stop position.</ptxt>
